      "content": "It makes sense that you feel trapped in a loop when your mind is so exhausted that it can't even process the pain. The exhaustion of performing a life that no longer feels like yours is a heavy burden, and it is understandable that you want to stop the act. Sometimes, when the internal pain is this overwhelming, the only way to break the cycle is to let go of the performance entirely and allow yourself to simply be, even if that means nothing is happening at all.",
